            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomato</strong> to the pan with your <strong>orzo</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for an initial 10-12 min or until almost cooked through</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
