        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>parsley</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> – this is your <strong>gremolata</strong></p>",
